**1. Description of the problem:**
In the following example, `JsonPatchDocument.ApplyTo` throws a `NullReferenceException` when the patch to the object wrapper is applied. I would expect it to throw a `JsonPatchException` in this case.  

When a dynamic object is used throughout then a `JsonPatchException` with a meaningful error message is thrown.

In both cases, the object that the patch is being applied to has the structure:
```json
{
  Object: {
    hello: "world"
  }
}
```

**2. Steps to reproduce (preferrably a link to a GitHub repo with a repro project)**
```c#
using System;
using System.Dynamic;

using Microsoft.AspNetCore.JsonPatch;

public class Program
{
    static void Main(string[] args)
    {
        var jsonPatchDocument = new JsonPatchDocument();
        jsonPatchDocument.Move("/Object", "/Object/goodbye");

        dynamic @object = new ExpandoObject();
        @object.hello = "world";

        // throws JsonPatchException
        try
        {
            dynamic objectToApplyTo = new ExpandoObject();
            objectToApplyTo.Object = @object;
            jsonPatchDocument.ApplyTo(objectToApplyTo);
        }
        catch (Exception exception)
        {
            Console.WriteLine(exception);
        }

        // throws NullReferenceException
        try
        {
            var objectToApplyTo = new ObjectWrapper();
            objectToApplyTo.Object = @object;
            jsonPatchDocument.ApplyTo(objectToApplyTo);
        }
        catch (Exception exception)
        {
            Console.WriteLine(exception);
        }

        Console.ReadKey();
    }

    private class ObjectWrapper
    {
        public dynamic Object { get; set; }
    }
}
```

