Consider:
```C#
[Route("/[controller]/[action]")]
[Test]
public class HomeController : Controller
{
    [HttpDelete]
    public IActionResult Index() => View("/Pages/Index.cshtml");

    public IActionResult Index2() => View("/Pages/Index.cshtml");

}

public class Test : Attribute, IActionHttpMethodProvider
{
    public IEnumerable<string> HttpMethods => new[] { "GET", "PUT" };
}
```


With 2.1 routing, GET, PUT, DELETE on /Home/Index -> 404
With 2.2 routing, GET, PUT on /Home/Index -> 405. DELETE -> 200

Filing an issue so we know are aware of this change in behavior

